filter.description:
Filtering multiple key/value pairs
Operator     |   Description
==     |   Case insensitive match with pattern.
!=     |    Does not match with pattern (case insensitive).
=@     |    Pattern found in object value (case insensitive).
!@     |    ﻿Pattern not﻿ found in object value (case insensitive).
<=     |    Value must be less than or equal to ﻿pattern﻿.
<     |    Value must be less than pattern﻿.
.>=    |    Value must be greater than or equal to ﻿pattern﻿.
.>     |    Value must be greater than ﻿pattern﻿.
Logical OR    |    Separate filters using commas ','
Logical AND    |    Filter strings can be combined to create logical AND queries by including multiple filters in the request.
Combining AND and OR    |    You can combine AND and OR filters together to create more complex filters.

stat-items.description: Items to count occurrence in entire response (multiple items should be separated by '|').

action.description:
If supported, an action can be specified.
_move_: Move this specific resource.
When *action=move* is set, one of the extra parameters (*before*, *after*) must be provided.
__*Note:*__ If this parameter is provided when not supported, the action will be ignored and an “invalid request” error will be returned.

before.description:
If *action=move*, use *before* to specify the ID of the resource that this resource will be moved before.
For example, to move `object 1` to before `object 2`, use:
__action=move&before=2__
__*Note:*__ This parameter can only be used when the *action* parameter is set to *move*.

after.description:
If *action=move*, use *after* to specify the ID of the resource that this resource will be moved after.
For example, to move `object 1` to after `object 3`, use:
__action=move&after=3__
__*Note:*__ This parameter can only be used when the *action* parameter is set to *move*.

options.help: Use PING to test the link with the server.
options.label: Ping

options.name: http
options.help: Use HTTP-GET to test the link with the server.
options.label: Http

options.name: tcp-connect
options.help: Use a full TCP connection to test the link with the server.
options.label: Tcp Connect

holddown-interval.name: holddown-interval
holddown-interval.help: Enable/disable holddown timer. Server will be considered active and reachable once the holddown period has expired (30 seconds).

translate-host.name: translate-host
translate-host.help: Enable/disable translation of hostname/IP from virtual server to real server.

ssh-client-cert.name: ssh-client-cert
ssh-client-cert.help: Set access-proxy SSH client certificate profile.

ssh-host-key-validation.name: ssh-host-key-validation
ssh-host-key-validation.help: Enable/disable SSH real server host key validation.

options.name: disable
options.help: Disable SSH real server host key validation.
options.label: Disable

options.name: enable
options.help: Enable SSH real server host key validation.
options.label: Enable

ssh-host-key.name: ssh-host-key
ssh-host-key.help: One or more server host key.

verify-cert.name: verify-cert
verify-cert.help: Enable/disable certificate verification of the real server.

application.name: application
application.help: SaaS application controlled by this Access Proxy.

persistence.name: persistence
persistence.help: Configure how to make sure that clients connect to the same server every time they make a request that is part of the same session.

http-cookie-domain-from-host.name: http-cookie-domain-from-host
http-cookie-domain-from-host.help: Enable/disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.

options.name: disable
options.help: Disable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP (use http-cooke-domain setting).
options.label: Disable

options.name: enable
options.help: Enable use of HTTP cookie domain from host field in HTTP.
options.label: Enable

http-cookie-domain.name: http-cookie-domain
http-cookie-domain.help: Domain that HTTP cookie persistence should apply to.

http-cookie-path.name: http-cookie-path
http-cookie-path.help: Limit HTTP cookie persistence to the specified path.

http-cookie-generation.name: http-cookie-generation
http-cookie-generation.help: Generation of HTTP cookie to be accepted. Changing invalidates all existing cookies.

http-cookie-age.name: http-cookie-age
http-cookie-age.help: Time in minutes that client web browsers should keep a cookie. Default is 60 minutes. 0 = no time limit.

http-cookie-share.name: http-cookie-share
http-cookie-share.help: Control sharing of cookies across API Gateway. Use of same-ip means a cookie from one virtual server can be used by another. Disable stops cookie sharing.

options.name: disable
options.help: Only allow HTTP cookie to match this API Gateway.
options.label: Disable

options.name: same-ip
options.help: Allow HTTP cookie to match any API Gateway with same IP.
options.label: Same Ip

https-cookie-secure.name: https-cookie-secure
https-cookie-secure.help: Enable/disable verification that inserted HTTPS cookies are secure.

options.name: disable
options.help: Do not mark cookie as secure, allow sharing between an HTTP and HTTPS connection.
options.label: Disable

options.name: enable
options.help: Mark inserted cookie as secure, cookie can only be used for HTTPS a connection.
options.label: Enable

saml-server.name: saml-server
saml-server.help: SAML service provider configuration for VIP authentication.

saml-redirect.name: saml-redirect
saml-redirect.help: Enable/disable SAML redirection after successful authentication.

options.name: disable
options.help: Do not support redirection after successful SAML authentication.
options.label: Disable

options.name: enable
options.help: Support redirection after successful SAML authentication.
options.label: Enable

ssl-dh-bits.name: ssl-dh-bits
ssl-dh-bits.help: Number of bits to use in the Diffie-Hellman exchange for RSA encryption of SSL sessions.

ssl-algorithm.name: ssl-algorithm
ssl-algorithm.help: Permitted encryption algorithms for the server side of SSL full mode sessions according to encryption strength.

options.name: high
options.help: High encryption. Allow only AES and ChaCha.
options.label: High

options.name: medium
options.help: Medium encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, and RC4.
options.label: Medium

options.name: low
options.help: Low encryption. Allow AES, ChaCha, 3DES, RC4, and DES.
options.label: Low
